         <listPerson>
            <person sex="1">
               <persName xml:lang="gez" xml:id="n1" type="birth">ተንሤ፡ ማሞ፡</persName>
               <persName xml:lang="gez" corresp="#n1" type="normalized">Tanśe Māmmo</persName>
               <persName xml:lang="gez" xml:id="n2" type="birth">ትንሳኤ፡ ማሞ፡</persName>
               <persName xml:lang="gez" corresp="#n2" type="normalized">Tǝnsāʾe Māmmo</persName>
               
               <persName>
                  <roleName type="title">bitwaddad, daǧǧāzmāč
               </roleName>
               </persName>
               
               
               
               <faith type="EOTC"/>
               
               
               <occupation type="political">governor</occupation>
               
               
               <floruit notBefore="1722" notAfter="1733">He was a nobleman who in late<date>1732</date> 
                  led a revolt against <persName ref="PRS5617IyasuII"/>
                  and the <placeName ref="LOC5284Qwara"/> faction at court. 
                  He was one of
                  <persName ref="PRS2377Bakaffa"> <roleName type="title">ʾaṣe</roleName>
                     Bakāffā</persName>'s favoured officials, 
                  serving as <persName ref="PRS9239TanseT"><roleName type="title">bitwaddad</roleName>Tanśe Māmmo</persName>
                   in <date>1722</date> and as 
                  <persName ref="PRS9239TanseT"><roleName type="title">daǧǧāzmāč
                  </roleName> Tanśe Māmmo </persName> and governor of <placeName ref="LOC2488Damot"/>. 
                  In <date>1731</date>, 
                  <persName ref="PRS5617IyasuII"><roleName type="title">ʾaṣe</roleName> ʾIyāsu II</persName> 
                  appointed him <persName ref="PRS9239TanseT"><roleName type="title">ʾazzāž</roleName> 
                     Tǝnsāʾe Māmmo</persName> of <placeName ref="LOC6376Yebaba"/>.
                  He was angered by the maneuvering at the court upon 
                  <persName ref="PRS2377Bakaffa"><roleName type="title">ʾaṣe</roleName> Bakāffā</persName>'s death in which <persName ref="PRS2682BerhanM"/>, wife of <persName ref="PRS2377Bakaffa"/>, <persName ref="PRS5617IyasuII"/>'s mother, 
                  and her <placeName ref="LOC5284Qwara"/> n relatives hastily and secretly crowned <persName ref="PRS5617IyasuII"/>, seizing control of throne and state. 
                  The rebellion he led lasted from <date>19 December 1732</date> to <date>2 January 1733</date> and involved eight days of siege of the royal compound. 
                  Tanśe and his allied group were finally defeated by <placeName ref="LOC5284Qwara"/>'s forces. 
                  He was captured and publicly hanged in <date>1733</date>.
                 </floruit>
               <death when="1733"/>
               
               
